{
  "description": "CRITICAL: Tests should be as clean as production code. Keep tests readable and maintainable, use descriptive test names, and follow FIRST principles (Fast, Independent, Repeatable, Self-validating, Timely).",
  "examples": [
    {
      "do": {
        "description": "Keep tests clean and maintainable",
        "content": [
          "Keep tests readable and maintainable",
          "Use descriptive test names",
          "Follow FIRST principles:",
          "  - Fast: Tests run quickly",
          "  - Independent: Tests don't depend on each other",
          "  - Repeatable: Tests work in any environment",
          "  - Self-validating: Tests have boolean output (pass/fail)",
          "  - Timely: Tests written at right time (before production code)",
          "",
          "Correct Examples (quality tests):",
          "test('calculates order total including tax and shipping', () => {",
          "  const order = createTestOrder({ subtotal: 100 });",
          "  const total = calculateTotal(order);",
          "  expect(total).toBe(115); // 100 + 10 tax + 5 shipping",
          "});",
          "",
          "Test Quality Requirements:",
          "- Test code as clean as production code",
          "- Clear, descriptive test names",
          "- Fast execution (milliseconds)",
          "- No dependencies between tests",
          "- Consistent pass/fail behavior"
        ]
      },
      "dont": {
        "description": "Don't let test code decay or skip tests",
        "content": [
          "Don't let test code decay",
          "Don't skip 'trivial' tests",
          "Don't make tests dependent on each other",
          "",
          "Wrong Examples (poor test quality):",
          "test('test1', () => {  // bad name",
          "  globalState.user = createUser(); // sets global state",
          "  expect(process()).toBe(true);",
          "});",
          "",
          "test('test2', () => {  // depends on test1!",
          "  expect(globalState.user.name).toBe('John');",
          "});",
          "",
          "Poor Test Quality Indicators (FIX):",
          "- Generic test names (test1, test2)",
          "- Tests depending on execution order",
          "- Slow tests (seconds per test)",
          "- Flaky tests (intermittent failures)",
          "- Commented-out tests",
          "- Skipped tests without tickets",
          "",
          "Improvement Actions:",
          "- Rename tests descriptively",
          "- Remove inter-test dependencies",
          "- Speed up slow tests",
          "- Fix or delete flaky tests",
          "- Unskip or delete skipped tests"
        ]
      }
    }
  ]
}



















































